The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Funds for rural projects

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Bhubaneswar, Dec. 7: In a boost to rural development in Orissa, the Centre has sanctioned Rs 6.48 lakh as the first instalment of its grant under the Swajaldhara scheme.

 State rural development minister Biswa Bhusan Harichandan met Union rural development minister Raghuvansh Prasad Singh during his visit to Delhi on October 25 and asked for additional central assistance under the Swajaldhara and total sanitation programmes.

 During the discussion, Harichandan apprised Singh of the status, progress and fiscal requirements of various Centre-sponsored projects, which are being executed by the rural development department, and presented a memorandum in this regard. 

 A meeting of the National Plan Approval Committee recently sanctioned Rs 6.48 crore under phase I of the Swajaldhara scheme for the current fiscal, Harichandan said. 

 The minister added that the funds would be utilised in 27 of the 30 districts in the state. 




